  "name": "Payment of Bonus Act, 1965",
  "shortName": "Bonus Act",
  "officialCitation": "The Payment of Bonus Act, 1965 (Act No. 21 of 1965), repealed and saved under section 69 of the Code on Wages, 2019.",
  "overview": "Historical central labour-law record governing statutory bonus for covered establishments and eligible employees before the Code on Wages, 2019 became operative on 21 November 2025. The Payment of Bonus Act, 1965 was repealed by section 69 of the Code on Wages, 2019, subject to its savings provisions. Current bonus obligations must be evaluated under Chapter IV of the Code on Wages, 2019 and the applicable Central or State rules and notifications. This record is retained for historical periods, legacy proceedings, saved actions and audit traceability.",
